        "content": "<p>Is there a more general notion of \"filter\" that doesn't have sets of subsets but rather sets of elements from a poset?</p>",
        "id": 409372677,
        "sender_full_name": "Martin Dvořák",
        "timestamp": 1703159875
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>There are Zulip threads from a year or so ago on that topic, and probably some mathlib3 PRs</p>",
        "id": 409373329,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1703160108
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Here's one <a href=\"#narrow/stream/113488-general/topic/Filter.20.28set.29.20vs.20filter.20.28poset.29/near/223946624\">from 3 years ago</a></p>",
        "id": 409373456,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1703160134
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Oh, I think it's <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Order.PFilter#doc\">docs#Order.PFilter</a> ?</p>",
        "id": 409373710,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1703160220
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>What does the operator <code>≤</code> on <code>PFilter</code> instances do?</p>",
        "id": 409377360,
        "sender_full_name": "Martin Dvořák",
        "timestamp": 1703161609
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It corresponds to inclusion of filters.</p>",
        "id": 409378252,
        "sender_full_name": "Yaël Dillies",
        "timestamp": 1703161945
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Note this does <strong>not</strong> match the order on <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Filter#doc\">docs#Filter</a>, which is reverse inclusion instead.</p>",
        "id": 409378974,
        "sender_full_name": "Yaël Dillies",
        "timestamp": 1703162220
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Anyway, <code>PFilter</code> and <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Order.Ideal#doc\">docs#Order.Ideal</a> are currently in a very state. I've been meaning to redo everything from scratch now that we have <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=UpperSet#doc\">docs#UpperSet</a>, <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=LowerSet#doc\">docs#LowerSet</a>, but I haven't yet found time to do so.</p>",
